President Obama has nominated Donald W. Beatty and Donald C. Coggins, Jr. to serve on the United States District Court for the District of South Carolina. Donald W. Beatty is currently an Associate Justice on the South Carolina Supreme Court and has a long history of judicial service. Donald C. Coggins, Jr. is a shareholder at a law firm in Spartanburg, South Carolina, with a focus on civil litigation. Both nominees are highly qualified and will be valuable additions to the United States District Court.